1
00:00:02,002 --> 00:00:02,878
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:02,878 --> 00:00:03,420
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:06,757
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:09,384 --> 00:00:10,385
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:10,427 --> 00:00:11,512
(QUACKS)

6
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:13,805
Adventure Time

7
00:00:13,931 --> 00:00:15,265
Come on, grab your friends

8
00:00:15,307 --> 00:00:17,893
We'll go to very distant lands

9
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:20,270
With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

10
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,147
The fun will never end

11
00:00:22,231 --> 00:00:24,107
It's Adventure Time

12
00:00:32,324 --> 00:00:34,326
STARCHY: Welcome back
to "Graveyard Shift".

13
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:36,078
I'm your host, Starchy.

14
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:37,955
You know what today is, everybody?

15
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,957
It's our fifth-anniversary show.

16
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:42,084
So many things have happened in that time.

17
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,919
I switched from drinking rainwater

18
00:00:43,961 --> 00:00:45,671
to eating distilled ice chips.

19
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:47,047
I took up rock climbing.

20
00:00:47,089 --> 00:00:48,215
My wife left me.

21
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:50,342
And all-new conspiracies.

22
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:51,969
I firmly believe

23
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:55,305
that all chocolate has been
secretly replaced by mud.

24
00:00:55,347 --> 00:00:59,309
And why is the burrito man
giving away free burritos?

25
00:00:59,351 --> 00:01:01,103
He's an amateur mad scientist

26
00:01:01,228 --> 00:01:02,938
trying to genetically change us into tortillas.

27
00:01:02,980 --> 00:01:04,690
(GROANS) Dude, come on.

28
00:01:04,815 --> 00:01:07,442
STARCHY: When was the last time
you sharpened your pencils, hmm?

29
00:01:07,526 --> 00:01:10,821
Never. They're pens
painted to look like pencils.

30
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:11,947
Conspiracy!

31
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,782
STARCHY: Okay, the board is lighting up.

32
00:01:13,824 --> 00:01:15,075
We're going to a caller.

33
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:16,827
You are on the air, caller.

34
00:01:16,952 --> 00:01:18,203
BANANA GUARD: (ON CALL)
I'm a Banana Guard.

35
00:01:18,287 --> 00:01:19,913
Oh. It's a good job to have.

36
00:01:19,955 --> 00:01:21,206
BANANA GUARD: Yeah, it's pretty good.

37
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:23,667
Why do they have it tuned
to this every time we're here?

38
00:01:23,709 --> 00:01:25,043
I call baloney!

39
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:27,337
Shh! I'm trying to listen
to the frightened caller.

40
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:31,341
BANANA GUARD: So, I think I might have
seen something not from this world.

41
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:32,593
STARCHY: Go ahead, caller.

42
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:34,052
BANANA GUARD: It happened last Sunday.

43
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:36,054
I was doing my laundry at the mat,

44
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:39,558
when I saw a reflection
of a girl with eerie blank eyes!

45
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:43,103
I turned around, but nobody was there.

46
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:44,605
It was scary.

47
00:01:44,688 --> 00:01:47,983
STARCHY: Yeah, weird girls
with soulless blank eyes.

48
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:51,737
They've been spotted around
multiple kingdoms across the centuries.

49
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:53,572
Nobody knows what they are,

50
00:01:53,614 --> 00:01:55,616
- but I have a few theories.
- (GRUMBLES)

51
00:01:55,741 --> 00:01:58,368
They're ghosts, and the last thing
they looked at in life

52
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:01,246
was so horrific, it made their eyes turn blank.

53
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:03,248
(BLOWS RASPBERRY) Baloney!

54
00:02:03,373 --> 00:02:04,374
The pizza.

55
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:06,710
(BLOWS RASPBERRY)

56
00:02:06,752 --> 00:02:07,753
Take the rest to go.

57
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:09,421
STARCHY: My second theory...

58
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:13,300
Okay, all boxed up and ready to go.
200 bucks.

59
00:02:13,383 --> 00:02:15,927
STARCHY: ... by other blank-eyed girls
touching their eyeballs.

60
00:02:16,011 --> 00:02:17,512
(SHUDDERS) Spooky!

61
00:02:17,554 --> 00:02:18,805
Ooh, look at me!

62
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:21,183
I'm listening to a dumb nonsense radio show!

63
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:23,810
How can you be so dismissive
after some of the stuff we've seen?

64
00:02:23,935 --> 00:02:26,938
You got to draw the line somewhere.
Starchy's my line.

65
00:02:27,022 --> 00:02:30,275
STARCHY: They're walking fish
that just happen to look like little girls.

66
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:32,819
- Baloney!
- Don't touch my radio!

67
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:36,698
FINN: It's dark.

68
00:02:37,699 --> 00:02:40,452
You're sure that blank-eyed girls
are made up, right?

69
00:02:40,577 --> 00:02:42,162
Yeah, man, it's all baloney.

70
00:02:42,204 --> 00:02:43,330
(OWL HOOTS)

71
00:02:43,413 --> 00:02:44,456
(SHUDDERS)

72
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:45,916
(CHUCKLES)

73
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:47,334
Jake?

74
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:50,796
Jake?

75
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:54,091
Uh...

76
00:02:54,341 --> 00:02:55,801
Blank-eyed girl?

77
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:57,427
- Boo!
- (SHRIEKS)

78
00:02:57,469 --> 00:02:58,804
(LAUGHS)

79
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:01,348
(BOTH LAUGHING)

80
00:03:01,473 --> 00:03:03,100
Boo!

81
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,351
(BOTH SIGH)

82
00:03:04,476 --> 00:03:06,436
(TWIGS SNAPPING)

83
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:08,939
(BOTH CHUCKLING NERVOUSLY)

84
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:12,567
(SNAPPING CONTINUES)

85
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:13,985
BOTH: Is this creeping you out?

86
00:03:14,111 --> 00:03:15,487
(BOTH LAUGH)

87
00:03:17,489 --> 00:03:18,865
(OWL HOOTS)

88
00:03:18,949 --> 00:03:19,950
(SNAPPING CONTINUES)

89
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:21,118
(BOTH SCREAM)

90
00:03:21,201 --> 00:03:22,619
BOTH: Can I hold your hand?

91
00:03:22,619 --> 00:03:24,246
- BOTH: Yes.
- (LEAVES RUSTLE)

92
00:03:25,831 --> 00:03:26,873
(BOTH GASP)

93
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:29,876
(BOTH PANTING)

94
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:33,964
(BOTH SHOUTING)

95
00:03:35,465 --> 00:03:37,509
(BOTH LAUGHING)

96
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:40,011
- That was stupid.
- Yeah. Stupid.

97
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:41,471
(SCRATCHING)

98
00:03:41,513 --> 00:03:42,639
(BOTH GASP)

99
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:44,015
Are you messing with me?

100
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:45,851
Uh-uh. You're messing with me.

101
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:46,977
(SCRATCHING)

102
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:48,770
Must be someone else.

103
00:03:48,854 --> 00:03:50,647
Yeah, like, Ice King, maybe.

104
00:03:54,359 --> 00:03:55,485
(BOTH SCREAM)

105
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:58,905
- Who was that?
- Maybe it was nobody.

106
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:02,409
Courage, courage.

107
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:03,785
What's wrong with me?

108
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:06,288
That could be a normal little girl
who needs help.

109
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:08,498
(SHUDDERING) No!

110
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:10,625
- (DOOR SLAMS SHUT)
- (BOTH SHRIEK)

111
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,669
- (SCREAMS) There! Blank-eyed girl!
- (GASPS)

112
00:04:12,753 --> 00:04:14,296
(BOTH SCREAMING)

113
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:18,759
She's too creepy, man!

114
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:20,719
I know! I know!

115
00:04:20,761 --> 00:04:22,262
But I got an idea.

116
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:23,889
Welcome, next caller.

117
00:04:24,014 --> 00:04:25,265
FINN: Hello, Starchy? Am I on?

118
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:26,641
STARCHY: Yeah, you're on.

119
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:28,518
Longtime listener, first-time caller.

120
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:31,521
STARCHY: We got the wonderful
Finn the human on the phone.

121
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:32,856
Go ahead, Finn.

122
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:35,901
Starchy, I'm in a blank-eyed girl
situation right now.

123
00:04:35,901 --> 00:04:37,110
What should I do?

124
00:04:37,152 --> 00:04:39,029
I'm going upstairs to get a better look.

125
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:41,782
STARCHY: All right, stay calm.
You called the right guy.

126
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:44,284
The question is, why did she choose you?

127
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:47,245
- Are these visits random events?
- (GASPS)

128
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:51,416
(WHIMPERS)

129
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:52,667
- Jake.
- (SHRIEKS)

130
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:57,672
STARCHY: Finn, have you invited
the blank-eyed girl inside?

131
00:04:57,672 --> 00:04:58,799
No. Why?

132
00:04:58,882 --> 00:05:01,802
STARCHY: Because I believe the girls
have to follow vampire rules.

133
00:05:01,927 --> 00:05:04,387
As long as you don't invite her in,
you should be fine.

134
00:05:04,429 --> 00:05:06,181
Okay. Let me write this down.

135
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:07,682
Oop.

136
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:14,815
Starchy? She invited herself in.

137
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:16,441
STARCHY: Eh... Run!

138
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:23,073
(WHISPERING)
Starchy, she's staring right at us!

139
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:25,575
Oh! I got it! Fairy rules.

140
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:28,328
Try offering her some cream in a saucer.

141
00:05:28,411 --> 00:05:30,580
That should appease
the blank-eyed girl's hunger

142
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:31,790
and send her away.

143
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:32,958
Gotcha.

144
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:34,084
(INHALES SHARPLY)

145
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:35,919
- Jake, go get the cream.
- What?

146
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:38,421
No! You go! This is your deal!

147
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:39,923
Just go...

148
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:41,466
Okay! Geez!

149
00:05:41,550 --> 00:05:42,717
Thank you.

150
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:45,679
(HAIR RUSTLING)

151
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:49,224
Okay. Cream.

152
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:58,859
(GROANS)

153
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:01,236
- (GLASS SHATTERS)
- (SHRIEKING)

154
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:03,613
- Ugh!
- Starchy?

155
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:05,490
Mmm. Didn't work, huh?

156
00:06:05,574 --> 00:06:06,950
Must be a haint, then.

157
00:06:06,992 --> 00:06:10,370
Try playing the clarinet.
Haints hate the clarinet.

158
00:06:11,454 --> 00:06:12,706
(GROANS)

159
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:15,709
(CLARINET PLAYING)

160
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:19,838
I think it's working! Keep playing!

161
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,756
(CLARINET CONTINUES)

162
00:06:23,258 --> 00:06:24,509
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

163
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:25,886
Uh...

164
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:32,893
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

165
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:38,982
Jake, stop!

166
00:06:41,151 --> 00:06:43,987
Starchy, I think they like the clarinet music!
Also, there's six of them now!

167
00:06:44,029 --> 00:06:47,032
Jeepers! Really? Eh... Uh, okay.

168
00:06:47,157 --> 00:06:50,619
Now I definitely know
what you're dealing with. An undead.

169
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:54,414
The undead fear the gaze
of the common yard chicken.

170
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:56,124
Our chicken ran away though.

171
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:57,667
(GRUMBLES)

172
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:01,671
Are you sure we need the feathers?

173
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:03,423
My chicken's pretty spot-on.

174
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:05,508
We don't want to take
any chances, you know?

175
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:06,635
Hmph.

176
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:07,761
Hey!

177
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,681
(CROWING)

178
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:16,061
All this advice is just made-up baloney!

179
00:07:16,645 --> 00:07:18,813
Starchy, all your advice is made-up baloney!

180
00:07:19,648 --> 00:07:20,899
Aww.

181
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:23,068
Well, what are we supposed to do?
Just live with this?

182
00:07:24,903 --> 00:07:28,531
No more relying on hearsay.
We're gonna take it to the source.

183
00:07:30,575 --> 00:07:32,202
Secondary source.

184
00:07:36,331 --> 00:07:39,584
Girl stuff, boy stuff, ear stuff, butt stuff.

185
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:41,211
Hey! Creepy stuff!

186
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:43,588
(BOTH GRUNT)

187
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:44,714
Got it.

188
00:07:45,048 --> 00:07:46,216
(BOTH SHRIEK)

189
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:47,592
Shh.

190
00:07:47,676 --> 00:07:50,053
Library's closed.

191
00:07:50,095 --> 00:07:52,555
Turtle Princess! Did you dye your hair?

192
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:56,184
Oh yeah, I did. Do you like it?

193
00:07:56,226 --> 00:07:57,727
Yeah. Hotness.

194
00:07:57,852 --> 00:08:01,064
Say, do you know anything
about creepy blank-eyed girls?

195
00:08:01,106 --> 00:08:03,441
No, but I can find out.

196
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:07,737
"Creepy blank-eyed girls." Oh!

197
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:11,992
Says here they're an urban legend
that first appeared five years ago.

198
00:08:12,117 --> 00:08:14,369
- They're supposedly...
- Wait, five years ago?

199
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:16,746
That's... That's just like Starchy's radio show.

200
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:18,123
(GASPS DEEPLY)

201
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:19,374
Maybe they're tulpas!

202
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:21,209
What the blob is a tulpa?

203
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:23,878
Physical manifestations
of concentrated collective thought.

204
00:08:23,962 --> 00:08:27,757
They're entities who depend on the energy
of people believing in them in order to exist.

205
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:29,759
People like Starchy's listeners.

206
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:31,136
Okay.

207
00:08:31,261 --> 00:08:33,430
And where did you learn
all this blobbity-bob?

208
00:08:33,430 --> 00:08:37,058
Starchy's radio show.
I think T know what we need to do.

209
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:39,686
Thanks, Turtle P. (GRUNTS)

210
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:41,563
TURTLE PRINCESS: (MUFFLED)
Any time, Finny.

211
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:45,775
JAKE: Why don't we call, like, child services?
Or an exterminator?

212
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:47,944
This is gonna work. Just trust me, a'ight?

213
00:08:48,028 --> 00:08:49,154
Ugh.

214
00:08:50,572 --> 00:08:52,073
Do as I do.

215
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:54,951
(GIRLS EXHALE)

216
00:08:55,035 --> 00:08:56,703
(INHALES DEEPLY)

217
00:08:56,828 --> 00:09:00,040
Boy, I just love walking through
our delightfully not-creepy doorway.

218
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,958
- Don't you, Jake?
- Uh-huh, uh-huh.

219
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,793
(SHRIEKING)

220
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:05,962
Walking through the not-creepy air

221
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:08,965
to my not-creepy couch,
sitting on my not-creepy butt.

222
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:11,926
(CHUCKLES) Your butt is kinda creepy.

223
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:14,304
I say "creepy" is just another label we use

224
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:16,681
to distance ourselves from stuff
we don't understand.

225
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,475
- (GASPING)
- Or that it reminds us of something

226
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:20,310
in ourselves that we're not comfortable with.

227
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:21,436
Hmm.

228
00:09:21,478 --> 00:09:25,482
I mean, it just ain't an actual thing, you know?
Unless you choose to believe it.

229
00:09:25,607 --> 00:09:26,691
Right, Jake?

230
00:09:26,733 --> 00:09:28,359
(DEEP SIGH)

231
00:09:28,443 --> 00:09:31,112
It's baloney! It's baloney!
It's Starchy's baloney!

232
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:33,198
I just got to think of something wholesome.

233
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:37,827
- (SPEAKS KOREAN)
- (JAKE SCREAMS)

234
00:09:39,704 --> 00:09:41,456
- (WAILING)
- (JAKE SCREAMS)

235
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:44,125
(JAKE BREATHING HEAVILY)

236
00:09:44,501 --> 00:09:46,878
(SCREAMING) No!

237
00:09:46,961 --> 00:09:48,755
Pizza's creepy now!

238
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:50,507
(CRYING)

239
00:09:50,632 --> 00:09:52,092
You win, all right?

240
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:53,635
You're mad-creepy!

241
00:09:53,635 --> 00:09:56,513
Do what you will,
you globless, blank-eyed girls!

242
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:01,976
Uh...

243
00:10:02,227 --> 00:10:03,394
(GASPS) What?

244
00:10:07,482 --> 00:10:08,900
What the butt fuzz?

245
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:11,361
Contact lenses?

246
00:10:11,903 --> 00:10:13,780
Ha! Baloney.

247
00:10:13,863 --> 00:10:16,741
Nothing but some kids playing a dumb prank!

248
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:22,163
Man. This whole time,
they were just regular girls.

249
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:23,665
Where are your parents, huh?

250
00:10:23,665 --> 00:10:26,417
You guys are going to jail! You hear?

251
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:35,009
So, y'all are bald. Good job.

252
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,928
I'm still calling the cops.

253
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:39,430
(SQUEAKING)

254
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:48,398
(POPS)

255
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:56,030
(BOTH WHIMPERING)

256
00:10:56,573 --> 00:10:59,200
